===Verb===
{{en-verb|whitewash|es}}

# To paint over with a lime and water mixture so as to brighten up a wall or fence.
#: ''The houses looked very bright when they '''whitewashed''' the whole neighborhood''.
# {{context|idiomatic|lang=en}} To cover over errors or bad actions.
#: ''In his sermon, the minister didn't try to '''whitewash''' over the sins of his church''.
# {{context|dated|transitive|lang=en}} To [[repay]] the [[financial]] [[debt]]s of (another person).
#: {{rfquotek|Charles Dickens, ''The Pickwick Papers''}}
# {{context|baseball|slang|dated|late|19th century|archaic|lang=en}} To prevent a team from scoring any runs.
# {{context|acting|lang=en}} To choose [[white]] film or television actors to portray characters that were Asian, African, or other races.
# {{context|pejorative|lang=en}} To [[make over]] (an Asian, African, or person of another race, especially a woman) to look Caucasian.

